name: restart_syscall
description: Restart a system call that was interrupted by a signal.

name: exit
description: Terminates the calling process with an exit status.
use_case: Exiting a program cleanly with a status code.

name: fork
description: Creates a new process by duplicating the calling process.
use_case: Creating a new process in a shell or server.

name: read
description: Uses a file descriptor to read bytes from an underlying resource (e.g., file, pipe, socket) into a buffer.
use_case: Reading user input from stdin or data from a file.

name: write
description: Uses a file descriptor to write bytes from a buffer to an underlying resource (e.g., file, pipe, socket).
use_case: Writing logs to a file or output to the terminal.

name: open
description: Opens a file or resource and returns a file descriptor for accessing it.
use_case: Opening a configuration file for reading.

name: close
description: Closes the file descriptor, releasing the resource it refers to.
use_case: Closing a file after reading or writing is done.

name: creat
description: Creates a new file or rewrites an existing one.

name: link
description: Creates a new link (hard link) to an existing file.

name: unlink
description: Deletes a name and possibly the file it refers to.
use_case: Deleting a temporary or obsolete file.

name: execve
description: Executes a program, replacing the current process image.
use_case: Running a new program from a shell.

name: chdir
description: Changes the current working directory of the calling process.

name: mknod
description: Creates a filesystem node (file, device special file).

name: chmod
use_case: Changing permissions of a newly created file.

name: lchown
description: Changes the owner and group of a file without following symbolic links.

name: lseek
description: Repositions the offset of the file descriptor within the associated file.
use_case: Seeking to the end of a file before appending data.

name: getpid
description: Returns the process ID (PID) of the calling process.
use_case: Getting the current process ID for logging or control.

name: mount
description: Mounts a filesystem.

name: setuid
use_case: Dropping privileges in a setuid program for security.

name: getuid
description: Returns the real user ID of the calling process.

name: ptrace
description: Provides a means by which a process can observe and control another process.

name: pause
description: Waits for a signal to arrive.

name: access
description: Checks a user's permissions for a file.

name: nice
description: Changes the scheduling priority of a process.

name: sync
description: Flushes filesystem buffers.

name: kill
use_case: Sending signals to terminate or control other processes.

name: rename
description: Renames a file or directory.

name: mkdir
description: Creates a new directory.

name: rmdir
description: Removes an empty directory.

name: dup
description: Creates a copy of a file descriptor referring to the same open file description.
use_case: Redirecting stdout to a file using file descriptor duplication.

name: pipe
description: Creates a unidirectional data channel that can be used for interprocess communication.

name: times
description: Returns process times.

name: brk
description: Changes the end of the data segment to allocate or deallocate memory.

name: setgid
description: Sets the group ID of the calling process.

name: getgid
description: Returns the real group ID of the calling process.

name: geteuid
description: Returns the effective user ID of the calling process.

name: getegid
description: Returns the effective group ID of the calling process.

name: acct
description: Enables or disables process accounting.

name: ioctl
description: Performs a device-specific operation on a file descriptor.

name: fcntl
description: Performs operations on a file descriptor (e.g., locks, flags).

name: setpgid
description: Sets the process group ID for job control.

name: umask
description: Sets the calling process's file mode creation mask.

name: chroot
description: Changes the root directory of the calling process.

name: ustat
description: Returns information about a mounted filesystem (obsolete).

name: dup2
description: Duplicates a file descriptor to a specified value.

name: getppid
description: Returns the parent process ID.

name: getpgrp
description: Returns the process group ID of the calling process.

name: setsid
description: Creates a new session and sets the process group ID.

name: sigaction
description: Examines and changes a signal action.

name: setreuid
description: Sets real and effective user IDs.

name: setregid
description: Sets real and effective group IDs.

name: sigsuspend
description: Replaces the signal mask and waits for a signal.

name: sigpending
description: Examines pending signals.

name: sethostname
description: Sets the hostname of the machine.

name: setrlimit
description: Sets resource limits.

name: getrusage
description: Returns resource usage measures for the calling process.

name: gettimeofday
description: Gets the current time.

name: settimeofday
description: Sets the current time.

name: getgroups
description: Gets supplementary group IDs.

name: setgroups
description: Sets supplementary group IDs.

name: symlink
description: Creates a symbolic link.

name: readlink
description: Reads the value of a symbolic link.

name: uselib
description: Loads a shared library (obsolete).

name: swapon
description: Enables swapping on a device.

name: reboot
description: Reboots or shuts down the system.

name: munmap
description: Unmaps a previously mapped region of memory.
use_case: Releasing a previously mapped memory region.

name: truncate
description: Truncates a file to a specified length.

name: ftruncate
description: Truncates an open file to a specified length.

name: fchmod
description: Changes the permissions of a file via its file descriptor.

name: fchown
description: Changes the owner and group of a file via its file descriptor.

name: getpriority
description: Gets the scheduling priority of a process.

name: setpriority
description: Sets the scheduling priority of a process.

name: statfs
description: Returns information about a mounted filesystem.

name: fstatfs
description: Gets file system statistics for the file referred to by a file descriptor.

name: syslog
description: Writes or reads kernel messages.

name: setitimer
description: Sets a timer.

name: getitimer
description: Gets the current value of a timer.

name: stat
description: Returns file status.
use_case: Checking file metadata such as size or timestamps.

name: lstat
description: Returns file status, not following symbolic links.

name: fstat
description: Gets the status of a file via its file descriptor.

name: vhangup
description: Simulates a hangup on the current terminal.

name: wait4
use_case: Waiting for a child process to finish execution.

name: swapoff
description: Disables swapping on a device.

name: sysinfo
description: Returns system statistics.

name: fsync
description: Flushes all buffered modifications of a file to disk, using its file descriptor.

name: sigreturn
description: Restores signal context and returns from a signal handler.

name: clone
description: Creates a child process with specified sharing of resources.
use_case: Creating threads or lightweight processes in user programs.

name: setdomainname
description: Sets the NIS domain name.

name: uname
description: Returns system information.

name: adjtimex
description: Tunes the kernel's clock.

name: mprotect
description: Changes the access protections for a memory mapping.

name: sigprocmask
description: Examines and changes the signal mask.

name: init_module
description: Loads a kernel module.

name: delete_module
description: Removes a loaded kernel module.

name: quotactl
description: Enables or disables disk quotas.

name: fchdir
description: Changes the current working directory to that referred to by a file descriptor.
